    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Kristóf Batthyány (Prague, 21 January 1544)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Oláh has understood from Batthyány's letter what he
                            wants him to do: if the King sends him as a legate or on some other
                            official trip, Oláh should promote Battyhány’s affairs alongside the
                            ruler. Now the King is sending Battyhány to Zagreb, to the Slavonian
                            assembly. Oláh asks Battyhány to promote the recovery of both the
                            possessions of Oláh’s friends and his own tithe, as the King has
                            ordered. The King has not responded to the letter regarding Batthyány’s
                            payment, but Oláh will be on it. The King says about donating Gyulai’s
                            estates that this cannot be done while Gyulai’s son is alive; so Oláh
                            now turns to Batthyány, thinking that the King will listen to the
                            servitors’ advice once Gyulai dies.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Salutem plurimam et mei commendationem, Magnifice Domine et Amice
                        Honorandissime!<note xml:id="note.1">Kristóf Batthyány (†1571) was Royal
                        Grand-cup-bearer from 1534 until his death, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Fallenbüchl</hi> 1988, 91.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Ex litteris<note xml:id="note.2">We do not know this letter.</note>
                    Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae mihi redditis intellexi, quibus in rebus meam
                    desideret operam. Si quae res et occasio occurrerit, in qua Dominatio Vestra
                        <persName>suae maiestati</persName><note xml:id="note.3">King Ferdinand
                        I.</note> servire possit, sive in legatione obeunda, sive in aliis negotiis
                    curandis, ego ero apud maiestatem suam regiam, dominum nostrum clementissimum
                    sollicitator Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae. Maiestas sua hanc eiusdem
                    oblationem serviendi clementer et audivit et accepit. Nunc sua maiestas
                    Dominationem Vestram ad conventum Sclavonium <placeName>Zagrabis</placeName>
                    celebrandum designavit. Quam rogo, velit ibi bonis meis amicis et promotor esse
                    in decimis meis restituendis, sicuti maiestas sua mandavit. <choice>
                        <orig>De litteris</orig>
                        <supplied>Ad litteras</supplied>
                    </choice> ad <persName>Albertum praepositum</persName><note xml:id="note.4"
                        >Albert Peregi.</note> pro restitutione salarii dandas nondum sua maiestas
                    respondit, ego tamen suam maiestatem sollicitabo. De bonis
                        <persName>Gywlai</persName><note xml:id="note.5">István Gyulai was <hi
                            rend="italic">viceispán</hi> of Varasd county and a retainer <hi
                            rend="italic">(familiaris)</hi> of the Batthyány family. See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Terbe</hi> 2010, 60, and 66.</note><del corresp="Olahus"
                        >petendis</del> Dominationi Vestrae Magnificae dandis respondit sua
                    maiestas, quod interea, dum vivit adhuc filius illius unus,<note xml:id="note.6"
                        >János Gyulai (†1567), Ferenc Batthyány became his
                        guardian.</note><milestone unit="pb"/> non potest cuipiam conferre bona
                    illius legitime. Advertar igitur Dominationem Vestram de illius vivi adhuc filii
                    vel morte, vel vita, et quamprimum eius exitum significet, maiestatem suam
                    arbitror rationem servitiorum Dominationi Vestrae habituram. Ego vero in his,
                    quibus a me fieri poterit, ero sincerus amicus et servitor Dominationis Vestrae,
                    quae valeat feliciter, et me habeat commendatum.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Praga</placeName><del corresp="Olahus">11</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">21</add>. Ianuarii anno 1544.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">
                    <seg type="signature">Vester Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Zagrabiensis etc. sua
                        manu</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Magnifico domino Christophori de Bathyan pincernarum regalium
                    magistro, et consiliario regio etc. domino et amico honorandissimo.</p>
            </div>
